00:08:45.600 --> 00:08:47.225 align:middle line:84%
You're in the epicenter,
New York City.

00:08:47.225 --> 00:08:50.610 align:middle line:84%
Things got really quiet and
pretty still and for some

00:08:50.610 --> 00:08:52.260 align:middle line:90%
people, very depressing.

00:08:52.260 --> 00:08:56.012 align:middle line:84%
How did people deal
with the little d?

00:08:56.012 --> 00:08:57.720 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: I'll tell
you this, you know,

00:08:57.720 --> 00:08:59.760 align:middle line:90%
and I say this somberly.

00:08:59.760 --> 00:09:01.930 align:middle line:84%
There was a lot of
drinking going on.

00:09:01.930 --> 00:09:05.138 align:middle line:84%
There was a lot of imbibing
of social media going on.

00:09:05.138 --> 00:09:06.930 align:middle line:84%
There was a lot of
binge watching going on,

00:09:06.930 --> 00:09:08.110 align:middle line:90%
not always a bad thing.

00:09:08.110 --> 00:09:08.910 align:middle line:90%
I mean, we all--

00:09:08.910 --> 00:09:10.700 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I'll do binge
watching if it's fun.

00:09:10.700 --> 00:09:11.380 align:middle line:90%
I like it too.

00:09:11.380 --> 00:09:12.810 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: We need to
unplug from time to time

00:09:12.810 --> 00:09:14.130 align:middle line:90%
and it's necessary.

00:09:14.130 --> 00:09:16.810 align:middle line:84%
I tend to binge watch
World War I documentaries,

00:09:16.810 --> 00:09:20.740 align:middle line:84%
which is not an ideal way
to unplug, but that's me.

00:09:20.740 --> 00:09:26.670 align:middle line:84%
But I think that people were
and are dealing with depression.

00:09:26.670 --> 00:09:28.990 align:middle line:84%
And New York is just
starting to come out of it.

00:09:28.990 --> 00:09:30.910 align:middle line:84%
But we're dealing with
the aftermath of it.

00:09:30.910 --> 00:09:32.370 align:middle line:90%
And it's very, very tough.

00:09:32.370 --> 00:09:33.810 align:middle line:84%
And this is one
of the reasons why

00:09:33.810 --> 00:09:36.570 align:middle line:84%
I want people to ask themselves
very serious questions

00:09:36.570 --> 00:09:38.790 align:middle line:84%
as if for the first time,
as if for the first time.

00:09:38.790 --> 00:09:39.610 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: This is
the time to do it.

00:09:39.610 --> 00:09:40.620 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: What do I want?

00:09:40.620 --> 00:09:41.430 align:middle line:90%
What do I want?

00:09:41.430 --> 00:09:43.847 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Like you said at the
beginning, this is a reset.

00:09:43.847 --> 00:09:46.680 align:middle line:84%
This is a chance to reset
society, cultures, everything.

00:09:46.680 --> 00:09:49.680 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: , Everything and
none of us particularly asked

00:09:49.680 --> 00:09:52.290 align:middle line:84%
for it, at least not
in a cognizant way.

00:09:52.290 --> 00:09:53.680 align:middle line:90%
But we received it.

00:09:53.680 --> 00:09:54.940 align:middle line:90%
We received it.

00:09:54.940 --> 00:09:57.570 align:middle line:84%
We have to ask ourselves
about college expenses.

00:09:57.570 --> 00:10:00.080 align:middle line:84%
We have to ask ourselves about
the scale of our household.

00:10:00.080 --> 00:10:01.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well let's
have the courage

00:10:01.140 --> 00:10:02.200 align:middle line:90%
to go there for a minute.

00:10:02.200 --> 00:10:03.000 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Please.

00:10:03.000 --> 00:10:07.170 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So many kids are
just dying on the vine.

00:10:07.170 --> 00:10:10.650 align:middle line:84%
This whole virtual school,
doing everything online

00:10:10.650 --> 00:10:14.310 align:middle line:84%
has just killed their
enthusiasm, interest, energy.

00:10:14.310 --> 00:10:16.320 align:middle line:84%
You know, so kids are
gaming late at night.

00:10:16.320 --> 00:10:19.200 align:middle line:84%
They don't even want to get up
and do these stupid classes.

00:10:19.200 --> 00:10:23.310 align:middle line:84%
And so this is bringing a
whole larger discussion up as

00:10:23.310 --> 00:10:25.560 align:middle line:84%
to the nature of
an education model

00:10:25.560 --> 00:10:27.720 align:middle line:84%
that was based in
the Industrial Age

00:10:27.720 --> 00:10:31.290 align:middle line:84%
to train people for specific
things, specific jobs,

00:10:31.290 --> 00:10:33.240 align:middle line:84%
to walk through a
specific door, to apply

00:10:33.240 --> 00:10:35.970 align:middle line:84%
for a specific thing,
most of which or much

00:10:35.970 --> 00:10:37.200 align:middle line:90%
of which is going away.

00:10:37.200 --> 00:10:38.658 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: No
question about that.

00:10:38.658 --> 00:10:43.620 align:middle line:84%
It's extremely important and
I really ask parents and kids

00:10:43.620 --> 00:10:46.620 align:middle line:84%
and caregivers to think
very, very carefully

00:10:46.620 --> 00:10:50.640 align:middle line:84%
about the cost-benefit
ratio of college,

00:10:50.640 --> 00:10:53.100 align:middle line:84%
about whether college
is going to steer you

00:10:53.100 --> 00:10:58.290 align:middle line:84%
on a path that's financially
stable, and personally happy,

00:10:58.290 --> 00:11:00.570 align:middle line:90%
personally rewarding.

00:11:00.570 --> 00:11:02.940 align:middle line:84%
Because I think I mean
certainly my generation

00:11:02.940 --> 00:11:06.900 align:middle line:84%
has operated for a long
time off of the model

00:11:06.900 --> 00:11:09.690 align:middle line:84%
that, well, if you
have a college degree

00:11:09.690 --> 00:11:12.330 align:middle line:84%
you can pull yourself up by
the bootstraps and so on and so

00:11:12.330 --> 00:11:12.510 align:middle line:90%
forth.

00:11:12.510 --> 00:11:13.410 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Not so much now.

00:11:13.410 --> 00:11:14.577 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Not so much now.

00:11:14.577 --> 00:11:17.620 align:middle line:84%
That's a post-war
baby boomer trope.

00:11:17.620 --> 00:11:18.420 align:middle line:90%
It's a trope.

00:11:18.420 --> 00:11:20.533 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's a trope
and we have to look at it.

00:11:20.533 --> 00:11:22.200 align:middle line:84%
And I was saying to
you before the show,

00:11:22.200 --> 00:11:26.670 align:middle line:84%
I always tell my kids you can be
an electrician who loves opera.

00:11:26.670 --> 00:11:28.590 align:middle line:84%
No one will ever be
able to export your job.

00:11:28.590 --> 00:11:30.960 align:middle line:84%
You're doing work that's
extremely important

00:11:30.960 --> 00:11:32.530 align:middle line:90%
and you're getting paid well.

00:11:32.530 --> 00:11:35.760 align:middle line:84%
And if you want to immerse
yourself in all the things

00:11:35.760 --> 00:11:37.770 align:middle line:84%
that are beautiful
and good in life,

00:11:37.770 --> 00:11:39.420 align:middle line:90%
you can do that in the trades.

00:11:39.420 --> 00:11:41.490 align:middle line:84%
The trades are a
wonderful career.

00:11:41.490 --> 00:11:43.000 align:middle line:84%
And I think we
really have to start

00:11:43.000 --> 00:11:45.250 align:middle line:90%
to wrap our arms around that.

00:11:45.250 --> 00:11:46.600 align:middle line:90%
I so agree with you.

00:11:46.600 --> 00:11:48.850 align:middle line:90%
I was just-- it just made me--

00:11:48.850 --> 00:11:51.070 align:middle line:84%
I was tickled to hear
you say it in that way.

00:11:51.070 --> 00:11:53.050 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't agree with
you more on this.

00:11:53.050 --> 00:11:56.050 align:middle line:84%
And this allows the
freedom of a young person

00:11:56.050 --> 00:11:58.300 align:middle line:84%
to actually start
resonating with something

00:11:58.300 --> 00:12:01.250 align:middle line:84%
rather than trying to fill
some industrialized slot

00:12:01.250 --> 00:12:02.110 align:middle line:90%
in the world.

00:12:02.110 --> 00:12:03.068 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Absolutely.

00:12:03.068 --> 00:12:05.590 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean, like
you say with your son,

00:12:05.590 --> 00:12:10.420 align:middle line:84%
there's a Matthew, Matthew
Crawford wrote a book called,

00:12:10.420 --> 00:12:13.930 align:middle line:90%
"Shop Class as Soul Craft."

00:12:13.930 --> 00:12:15.013 align:middle line:90%
Which I thought was--

00:12:15.013 --> 00:12:16.180 align:middle line:90%
I read that a few years ago.

00:12:16.180 --> 00:12:19.570 align:middle line:84%
I thought it was an
amazing book, looking at--

00:12:19.570 --> 00:12:22.210 align:middle line:84%
here is a man who
was in a think tank,

00:12:22.210 --> 00:12:26.200 align:middle line:84%
and really using his mind
strategically, very, very

00:12:26.200 --> 00:12:27.310 align:middle line:90%
mental process.

00:12:27.310 --> 00:12:30.278 align:middle line:84%
You never see an outcome of
anything at the end of the day.

00:12:30.278 --> 00:12:31.570 align:middle line:90%
You're just playing with ideas.

00:12:31.570 --> 00:12:34.540 align:middle line:84%
You go home and it's like
nothing has really happened.

00:12:34.540 --> 00:12:37.090 align:middle line:90%
His days seemed inconsequential.

00:12:37.090 --> 00:12:41.170 align:middle line:90%
So he decided the heck with it.

00:12:41.170 --> 00:12:43.480 align:middle line:84%
And he decided to go back
into something he adored,

00:12:43.480 --> 00:12:45.380 align:middle line:84%
which was motorcycle
maintenance.

00:12:45.380 --> 00:12:47.470 align:middle line:84%
And he took over a garage
and start repairing

00:12:47.470 --> 00:12:49.120 align:middle line:90%
the town's motorcycles.

00:12:49.120 --> 00:12:53.020 align:middle line:84%
And so people come in with their
stories, friendships are made.

00:12:53.020 --> 00:12:55.870 align:middle line:84%
Complex little
problems are solved

00:12:55.870 --> 00:12:59.410 align:middle line:84%
and you start feeling like
he had a life, a community.

00:12:59.410 --> 00:13:00.590 align:middle line:90%
Riff on that for a minute.

00:13:00.590 --> 00:13:02.257 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: It's
absolutely fascinating.

00:13:02.257 --> 00:13:04.300 align:middle line:84%
And I remember back when
I was in publishing,

00:13:04.300 --> 00:13:07.990 align:middle line:84%
oh man, this must be
going back about 20 years.

00:13:07.990 --> 00:13:11.890 align:middle line:84%
I was at Penguin which is
now Penguin Random House.

00:13:11.890 --> 00:13:13.900 align:middle line:84%
And I was sitting in
an editorial meeting

00:13:13.900 --> 00:13:16.420 align:middle line:84%
and I received a
proposal for a book.

00:13:16.420 --> 00:13:18.820 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't "Shop
Craft as Soul Craft."

00:13:18.820 --> 00:13:21.040 align:middle line:84%
But it even preceded
that book, in which

00:13:21.040 --> 00:13:23.290 align:middle line:84%
the author was making the
case that it was really time

00:13:23.290 --> 00:13:24.920 align:middle line:90%
to rethink college.

00:13:24.920 --> 00:13:26.980 align:middle line:90%
And I loved the book.

00:13:26.980 --> 00:13:28.643 align:middle line:84%
And my colleagues
stared at me blankly.

00:13:28.643 --> 00:13:30.310 align:middle line:84%
They just didn't get
it because they all

00:13:30.310 --> 00:13:32.170 align:middle line:84%
grew up with the
presumption that this

00:13:32.170 --> 00:13:33.740 align:middle line:84%
is the pathway to
the middle class.

00:13:33.740 --> 00:13:35.770 align:middle line:84%
And now what we're
seeing is, it's

00:13:35.770 --> 00:13:41.510 align:middle line:84%
in many cases, not all but many
a pathway to crushing debt.

00:13:41.510 --> 00:13:42.760 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Crushing the spirit.

00:13:42.760 --> 00:13:44.927 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Crushing the
spirit to great difficulty,

00:13:44.927 --> 00:13:48.490 align:middle line:84%
to getting to hemmed into
choices you might not want.

00:13:48.490 --> 00:13:50.440 align:middle line:84%
And of course, none
of this stuff is easy.

00:13:50.440 --> 00:13:51.640 align:middle line:90%
None of this stuff is easy.

00:13:51.640 --> 00:13:54.400 align:middle line:84%
If an individual unplugged
a white collar job

00:13:54.400 --> 00:13:56.740 align:middle line:84%
and goes into a more
craft based job,

00:13:56.740 --> 00:13:59.570 align:middle line:84%
he or she might have terrible
concerns about health care.

00:13:59.570 --> 00:14:02.530 align:middle line:84%
How do you pay for That these
are deadly serious issues.

00:14:02.530 --> 00:14:04.363 align:middle line:84%
And I'm with the
individual on these issues.

00:14:04.363 --> 00:14:05.822 align:middle line:84%
There's no hiding
from any of this.

00:14:05.822 --> 00:14:07.160 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's not easy.

00:14:07.160 --> 00:14:09.190 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: It's not easy
and it's very complex.

00:14:09.190 --> 00:14:10.670 align:middle line:90%
But we have to look at it.

00:14:10.670 --> 00:14:12.430 align:middle line:84%
I mean we're being
forced to look at it.

00:14:12.430 --> 00:14:15.370 align:middle line:90%
And it has to be treated--

00:14:15.370 --> 00:14:17.710 align:middle line:84%
we have to throw ourselves
into it with a certain degree

00:14:17.710 --> 00:14:18.490 align:middle line:90%
of energy.

00:14:18.490 --> 00:14:19.907 align:middle line:84%
Because whether
we like it or not,

00:14:19.907 --> 00:14:21.370 align:middle line:84%
these questions
are in front of us.

00:14:21.370 --> 00:14:24.070 align:middle line:84%
I know somebody who got
laid off from a finance job

00:14:24.070 --> 00:14:27.100 align:middle line:84%
back in the Great
Recession of 2008.

00:14:27.100 --> 00:14:28.630 align:middle line:90%
He had carpentry skills.

00:14:28.630 --> 00:14:30.110 align:middle line:90%
He became a carpenter.

00:14:30.110 --> 00:14:31.698 align:middle line:90%
He was enormously happy.

00:14:31.698 --> 00:14:33.490 align:middle line:84%
I'm not saying it's
the path for everybody,

00:14:33.490 --> 00:14:37.090 align:middle line:84%
but I've seen too many such
instances to just dismiss it

00:14:37.090 --> 00:14:37.900 align:middle line:90%
as a chimera.

00:14:37.900 --> 00:14:39.262 align:middle line:90%
I mean, these are real things.

00:14:39.262 --> 00:14:40.720 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They are,
and a lot of it

00:14:40.720 --> 00:14:44.200 align:middle line:84%
has to do with us parents
to start actually just

00:14:44.200 --> 00:14:47.410 align:middle line:84%
observing and watching where
our children's excitement is

00:14:47.410 --> 00:14:48.562 align:middle line:90%
coming from.

00:14:48.562 --> 00:14:50.770 align:middle line:84%
Because a lot of times we're
walking right past them.

00:14:50.770 --> 00:14:53.110 align:middle line:84%
We've got them shipped off
into this class and a tutor

00:14:53.110 --> 00:14:55.820 align:middle line:84%
here and music lessons
there and so forth.

00:14:55.820 --> 00:14:58.660 align:middle line:84%
And we're not really
watching what's

00:14:58.660 --> 00:15:01.390 align:middle line:84%
giving rise to increases
in their own excitement

00:15:01.390 --> 00:15:02.890 align:middle line:90%
and energy.

00:15:02.890 --> 00:15:05.560 align:middle line:84%
And I was interviewing
Michael Tellinger years

00:15:05.560 --> 00:15:08.890 align:middle line:84%
ago in his Ubuntu
Movement and talking

00:15:08.890 --> 00:15:11.410 align:middle line:84%
about mentorship
programs, where children

00:15:11.410 --> 00:15:15.560 align:middle line:84%
start showing their passions
and skills early in life.

00:15:15.560 --> 00:15:17.560 align:middle line:84%
And even at the age
of seven and eight,

00:15:17.560 --> 00:15:20.472 align:middle line:84%
pairing them with someone
who is skilled in that field.

00:15:20.472 --> 00:15:21.430 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Absolutely.

00:15:21.430 --> 00:15:23.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You know there's so
many creative ways to do this.

00:15:23.930 --> 00:15:27.200 align:middle line:84%
And it just makes me so happy
even having this conversation.

00:15:27.200 --> 00:15:30.135 align:middle line:84%
Because it's like human beings
get to buy their souls back.

00:15:30.135 --> 00:15:31.510 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Yes,
that's the wish.

00:15:31.510 --> 00:15:32.740 align:middle line:90%
That's the wish.

00:15:32.740 --> 00:15:34.330 align:middle line:84%
You know, I think
we're all going

00:15:34.330 --> 00:15:37.210 align:middle line:84%
to need to come to
terms with not only what

00:15:37.210 --> 00:15:39.790 align:middle line:90%
do we really want, but how--

00:15:39.790 --> 00:15:41.380 align:middle line:84%
this economy is never
going to go back

00:15:41.380 --> 00:15:42.910 align:middle line:84%
to the way it was
six months ago.

00:15:42.910 --> 00:15:44.350 align:middle line:84%
And none of us
know precisely what

00:15:44.350 --> 00:15:45.600 align:middle line:90%
that is going to look like.

00:15:45.600 --> 00:15:46.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It will be different.

00:15:46.420 --> 00:15:47.410 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: It'll be different.

00:15:47.410 --> 00:15:48.827 align:middle line:84%
And of course,
there's going to be

00:15:48.827 --> 00:15:51.490 align:middle line:84%
a need for medical
professionals and for engineers.

00:15:51.490 --> 00:15:54.250 align:middle line:84%
But there's also going to be
need for all kinds of jobs that

00:15:54.250 --> 00:15:55.660 align:middle line:84%
can't be outsourced,
whether it's

00:15:55.660 --> 00:15:59.240 align:middle line:84%
auto mechanic or
hairstylist or you name it.

00:15:59.240 --> 00:16:05.260 align:middle line:84%
And I think certainly, in
this past generation or two,

00:16:05.260 --> 00:16:08.980 align:middle line:84%
we have as a society,
made a terrible mistake

00:16:08.980 --> 00:16:12.310 align:middle line:84%
of failing to attach appropriate
prestige to those jobs.

00:16:12.310 --> 00:16:13.528 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, we have.

00:16:13.528 --> 00:16:15.070 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Those
are wonderful jobs.

00:16:15.070 --> 00:16:16.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Calling
them blue collar.

00:16:16.930 --> 00:16:17.620 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Yeah, I
don't like any of that.

00:16:17.620 --> 00:16:19.162 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And
elevating white collar.

00:16:19.162 --> 00:16:19.962 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Amen.

00:16:19.962 --> 00:16:21.100 align:middle line:90%
I don't like any of that.

00:16:21.100 --> 00:16:23.530 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Right down to the
criminal justice system.

00:16:23.530 --> 00:16:25.300 align:middle line:84%
You can get away
with horrific crimes

00:16:25.300 --> 00:16:27.430 align:middle line:84%
if you have a white
collar, if you

00:16:27.430 --> 00:16:29.432 align:middle line:90%
have a whiter, whitest collar.

00:16:29.432 --> 00:16:30.390 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Absolutely.

00:16:30.390 --> 00:16:32.515 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's pretty
sickening when you look back.

00:16:32.515 --> 00:16:35.560 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: A jet plane crashes
with 180 people on board,

00:16:35.560 --> 00:16:37.720 align:middle line:84%
there will never be any
criminal prosecutions.

00:16:37.720 --> 00:16:39.442 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's correct, yeah.

00:16:39.442 --> 00:16:41.900 align:middle line:84%
Well, we're on the same page
in virtually everything anyway

00:16:41.900 --> 00:16:42.900 align:middle line:90%
here.

00:16:42.900 --> 00:16:44.610 align:middle line:84%
So let's go back to
the notion of magic.

00:16:44.610 --> 00:16:47.630 align:middle line:84%
So we hear people thinking,
OK, I know what I want now.

00:16:47.630 --> 00:16:49.220 align:middle line:90%
How do I manifest this?

00:16:49.220 --> 00:16:53.370 align:middle line:84%
And you kind of look to your
book of magic or miracles

00:16:53.370 --> 00:16:54.870 align:middle line:90%
and you span all of them.

00:16:54.870 --> 00:16:56.170 align:middle line:90%
You use everything.

00:16:56.170 --> 00:16:58.170 align:middle line:84%
And so I'm just going to
read a couple of things

00:16:58.170 --> 00:16:59.820 align:middle line:84%
here, because this
is interesting.

00:16:59.820 --> 00:17:02.871 align:middle line:84%
The word magic itself
has a connotation.

00:17:02.871 --> 00:17:04.079 align:middle line:90%
Some people are afraid of it.

00:17:04.079 --> 00:17:05.470 align:middle line:90%
Some want to dive into it.

00:17:05.470 --> 00:17:08.819 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, and because of the notion
of black and white magic.

00:17:08.819 --> 00:17:09.630 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:17:09.630 --> 00:17:12.800 align:middle line:84%
So, and basically,
Aleister Crowley,

00:17:12.800 --> 00:17:15.359 align:middle line:84%
whose work you've also studied,
whom many people shudder

00:17:15.359 --> 00:17:16.470 align:middle line:90%
at the name of, right?

00:17:16.470 --> 00:17:19.349 align:middle line:84%
He's saying, simply
put the science and art

00:17:19.349 --> 00:17:23.460 align:middle line:84%
of causing change to occur
in conformity with will, that

00:17:23.460 --> 00:17:25.380 align:middle line:90%
is what he's calling magic.

00:17:25.380 --> 00:17:28.950 align:middle line:84%
I pulled that out of one, I
believe one of your articles.

00:17:28.950 --> 00:17:32.160 align:middle line:84%
The art and science of causing
change to occur in conformity

00:17:32.160 --> 00:17:33.270 align:middle line:90%
with our will.

00:17:33.270 --> 00:17:34.920 align:middle line:90%
Or I would say, desire.

00:17:34.920 --> 00:17:36.240 align:middle line:90%
OK, will or desire.

00:17:36.240 --> 00:17:37.790 align:middle line:84%
Singer wrote, and
you can tell us

00:17:37.790 --> 00:17:41.250 align:middle line:84%
who Singer is, we're all
black magicians in our dreams

00:17:41.250 --> 00:17:44.580 align:middle line:84%
and our fantasies,
perversions, and phobias.

00:17:44.580 --> 00:17:48.210 align:middle line:84%
So everyone has a little
bit of black magic.

00:17:48.210 --> 00:17:51.240 align:middle line:84%
If you're thinking
clearly an unkind thought,

00:17:51.240 --> 00:17:53.400 align:middle line:84%
and hermetics go
deeply into this,

00:17:53.400 --> 00:17:57.150 align:middle line:84%
if you're thinking an unkind
thought about this person

00:17:57.150 --> 00:18:02.220 align:middle line:84%
over there that is putting
out a thread of energy,

00:18:02.220 --> 00:18:04.080 align:middle line:90%
a thought form in the world.

00:18:04.080 --> 00:18:06.720 align:middle line:90%
That's black magic.

00:18:06.720 --> 00:18:08.250 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Well,
it's interesting.

00:18:08.250 --> 00:18:13.380 align:middle line:84%
And I have to say, I felt a
sense of great liberation,

00:18:13.380 --> 00:18:15.780 align:middle line:84%
personally speaking
in my search,

00:18:15.780 --> 00:18:19.170 align:middle line:84%
when I began pushing
away the idea of being

00:18:19.170 --> 00:18:21.030 align:middle line:84%
afraid of black
magic and turning

00:18:21.030 --> 00:18:23.610 align:middle line:84%
from black magic,
of averting my eyes

00:18:23.610 --> 00:18:25.080 align:middle line:90%
from so-called black magic.

00:18:25.080 --> 00:18:27.810 align:middle line:84%
And today, I think
we're in an era that's

00:18:27.810 --> 00:18:29.940 align:middle line:90%
beyond white and black magic.

00:18:29.940 --> 00:18:32.490 align:middle line:84%
I don't think that concept
serves us well anymore.

00:18:32.490 --> 00:18:34.155 align:middle line:84%
But to use the
old terms, I would

00:18:34.155 --> 00:18:36.030 align:middle line:84%
say if somebody asked
me for a definition of,

00:18:36.030 --> 00:18:38.520 align:middle line:84%
what do you mean when
you say black magic?

00:18:38.520 --> 00:18:41.430 align:middle line:84%
I mean very simply it's
my will be done versus thy

00:18:41.430 --> 00:18:42.330 align:middle line:90%
will be done.

00:18:42.330 --> 00:18:44.100 align:middle line:84%
We read in scripture,
thy will be done

00:18:44.100 --> 00:18:47.250 align:middle line:84%
and we write to merger will with
a higher will of the creator

00:18:47.250 --> 00:18:48.240 align:middle line:90%
or god.

00:18:48.240 --> 00:18:51.270 align:middle line:84%
I would have to say to be
plain, traditionally speaking,

00:18:51.270 --> 00:18:53.530 align:middle line:90%
black magic is my will be done.

00:18:53.530 --> 00:18:55.652 align:middle line:84%
However, I bring a
different wrinkle to it.

00:18:55.652 --> 00:18:58.110 align:middle line:84%
You mentioned the name Aleister
Crowley, and lots of people

00:18:58.110 --> 00:18:59.790 align:middle line:90%
cringe when they hear Crowley.

00:18:59.790 --> 00:19:03.780 align:middle line:84%
Crowley was a brilliant
magician, a brilliant artist,

00:19:03.780 --> 00:19:05.250 align:middle line:90%
a brilliant intellect.

00:19:05.250 --> 00:19:09.090 align:middle line:84%
Crowley, in my estimation
had a terrible ethical lapse.

00:19:09.090 --> 00:19:12.150 align:middle line:84%
And if he was living, I
wouldn't be one of his students.

00:19:12.150 --> 00:19:16.675 align:middle line:84%
Crowley, I think
was insufficiently--

00:19:16.675 --> 00:19:17.550 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Principled?

00:19:17.550 --> 00:19:18.967 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: --versed
or principled

00:19:18.967 --> 00:19:20.950 align:middle line:90%
in the idea of reciprocity.

00:19:20.950 --> 00:19:24.075 align:middle line:84%
Reciprocity, all of
life is one whole.

00:19:24.075 --> 00:19:25.450 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Will over others.

00:19:25.450 --> 00:19:28.150 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Yes,
will over others.

00:19:28.150 --> 00:19:31.590 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's what I consider
black magic, will over others.

00:19:31.590 --> 00:19:33.430 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: It's an
interesting question.

00:19:33.430 --> 00:19:35.080 align:middle line:90%
I sit with that question.

00:19:35.080 --> 00:19:37.810 align:middle line:84%
I do believe in
cosmic reciprocity.

00:19:37.810 --> 00:19:39.850 align:middle line:84%
Another person
might call it karma.

00:19:39.850 --> 00:19:42.070 align:middle line:84%
I do believe that
whatever I do to another,

00:19:42.070 --> 00:19:43.603 align:middle line:90%
I'm ultimately doing to myself.

00:19:43.603 --> 00:19:45.520 align:middle line:84%
And there's no question
about that in my mind.

00:19:45.520 --> 00:19:47.687 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, you have a
very high sense of ethics

00:19:47.687 --> 00:19:49.970 align:middle line:84%
and a very broad background
in the use of mind.

00:19:49.970 --> 00:19:51.220 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: I appreciate that.

00:19:51.220 --> 00:19:55.120 align:middle line:84%
So I really take very seriously
that whatever I'm doing

00:19:55.120 --> 00:19:56.590 align:middle line:90%
I'm ultimately doing to self.

00:19:56.590 --> 00:20:01.440 align:middle line:84%
I can't function without
an ethical backdrop.

00:20:01.440 --> 00:20:04.090 align:middle line:84%
Crowley did not have an ethical
backdrop and people around him

00:20:04.090 --> 00:20:05.200 align:middle line:90%
got hurt.

00:20:05.200 --> 00:20:07.720 align:middle line:84%
You could learn from
Crowley but you must,

00:20:07.720 --> 00:20:11.620 align:middle line:84%
must see the terrible
lapses in his character.

00:20:11.620 --> 00:20:13.510 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But it's
not just Crowley.

00:20:13.510 --> 00:20:16.600 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I've interviewed
many, many, many people.

00:20:16.600 --> 00:20:18.628 align:middle line:84%
And some of them I know
the personal side of.

00:20:18.628 --> 00:20:19.920 align:middle line:90%
They're not walking their talk.

00:20:19.920 --> 00:20:21.160 align:middle line:90%
We can just say that.

00:20:21.160 --> 00:20:22.118 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Absolutely.

00:20:22.118 --> 00:20:26.230 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: A lot of people are
brilliant in terms of content.

00:20:26.230 --> 00:20:28.010 align:middle line:90%
But they're not necessarily--

00:20:28.010 --> 00:20:30.800 align:middle line:90%
and what is the saying?

00:20:30.800 --> 00:20:32.770 align:middle line:84%
We teach best what
we need to learn.

00:20:32.770 --> 00:20:34.360 align:middle line:84%
And so a lot of
people I interview,

00:20:34.360 --> 00:20:37.168 align:middle line:84%
actually, well, a number of
them fall in that category.

00:20:37.168 --> 00:20:38.710 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: It's
the truth and we get

00:20:38.710 --> 00:20:40.330 align:middle line:90%
to see the sausages being made.

00:20:40.330 --> 00:20:43.510 align:middle line:84%
You know, when you know the
person behind the workshop,

00:20:43.510 --> 00:20:45.270 align:middle line:84%
you get to see the
sausages being made.

00:20:45.270 --> 00:20:46.450 align:middle line:90%
And it ain't always pretty.

00:20:46.450 --> 00:20:47.170 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No, it's not.

00:20:47.170 --> 00:20:49.170 align:middle line:84%
And it's surprising, some
of the people actually

00:20:49.170 --> 00:20:51.580 align:middle line:84%
that pose as the
greatest light are often

00:20:51.580 --> 00:20:53.320 align:middle line:90%
the ones that are doing harm.

00:20:53.320 --> 00:20:55.870 align:middle line:84%
And some of the
people that seem--

00:20:55.870 --> 00:20:58.480 align:middle line:84%
I remember interviewing-- I'm
not going to name his name.

00:20:58.480 --> 00:21:00.530 align:middle line:84%
I think we have him
in our archives here.

00:21:00.530 --> 00:21:02.170 align:middle line:84%
But when he came
into the studio,

00:21:02.170 --> 00:21:03.640 align:middle line:90%
everyone was like, oh my god.

00:21:03.640 --> 00:21:05.950 align:middle line:84%
You know it was like
darkness is coming our way.

00:21:05.950 --> 00:21:09.550 align:middle line:84%
This was one of the
sweetest hearts and kindest

00:21:09.550 --> 00:21:13.790 align:middle line:84%
men, gentleman like
in the heart, even.

00:21:13.790 --> 00:21:16.360 align:middle line:84%
And yet some of the
principles also aligned

00:21:16.360 --> 00:21:19.930 align:middle line:84%
with the intellectual
principles of Crowley.

00:21:19.930 --> 00:21:22.870 align:middle line:84%
So we ourselves need
to go out of fear

00:21:22.870 --> 00:21:24.160 align:middle line:90%
and have our own discernment.

00:21:24.160 --> 00:21:26.230 align:middle line:84%
Like, no, you crossed
the line there.

00:21:26.230 --> 00:21:27.380 align:middle line:90%
I don't believe that.

00:21:27.380 --> 00:21:29.260 align:middle line:90%
That's black magic to me.

00:21:29.260 --> 00:21:30.930 align:middle line:90%
May not be to someone else.

00:21:30.930 --> 00:21:32.680 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: I know who
you mean and I also

00:21:32.680 --> 00:21:33.370 align:middle line:90%
won't mention his name.

00:21:33.370 --> 00:21:35.770 align:middle line:84%
But I personally like him
because I know in his heart

00:21:35.770 --> 00:21:36.730 align:middle line:90%
he's an ethical person.

00:21:36.730 --> 00:21:37.240 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:21:37.240 --> 00:21:39.850 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: And I want people
to feel that their search has

00:21:39.850 --> 00:21:40.980 align:middle line:90%
no boundaries.

00:21:40.980 --> 00:21:43.120 align:middle line:84%
And I also want to
start to throw out

00:21:43.120 --> 00:21:44.350 align:middle line:90%
some of our vocabulary.

00:21:44.350 --> 00:21:47.000 align:middle line:84%
Because we hem people
into thinking like that's

00:21:47.000 --> 00:21:47.800 align:middle line:90%
a good person.

00:21:47.800 --> 00:21:49.090 align:middle line:90%
That's a bad person.

00:21:49.090 --> 00:21:51.970 align:middle line:84%
Whereas the actual
story of a person's life

00:21:51.970 --> 00:21:55.030 align:middle line:84%
can be very complex and can
have to do with what barriers

00:21:55.030 --> 00:21:57.430 align:middle line:84%
they're dealing with, what
they're pushing against,

00:21:57.430 --> 00:22:00.040 align:middle line:84%
who they are, their
sense of reciprocity.

00:22:00.040 --> 00:22:03.190 align:middle line:84%
And those who
advertise themselves

00:22:03.190 --> 00:22:08.180 align:middle line:84%
as being the whitest magic,
I mean, we've both seen it.

00:22:08.180 --> 00:22:11.410 align:middle line:84%
You part the curtain and there's
anger, there's desperation,

00:22:11.410 --> 00:22:14.110 align:middle line:84%
there's outburst, there's
humiliating other people.

00:22:14.110 --> 00:22:15.843 align:middle line:90%
And it can make you cynical.

00:22:15.843 --> 00:22:17.260 align:middle line:84%
But I would say,
don't be cynical.

00:22:17.260 --> 00:22:18.130 align:middle line:90%
Don't be cynical.

00:22:18.130 --> 00:22:19.510 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree with you.

00:22:19.510 --> 00:22:20.530 align:middle line:90%
Don't be cynical.

00:22:20.530 --> 00:22:22.600 align:middle line:90%
In fact, there are always tells.

00:22:22.600 --> 00:22:25.030 align:middle line:84%
When you're listening
to a person and you're

00:22:25.030 --> 00:22:26.500 align:middle line:90%
in a person's field.

00:22:26.500 --> 00:22:28.240 align:middle line:90%
How is this making me feel?

00:22:28.240 --> 00:22:30.250 align:middle line:84%
You know, they're speaking
sparkly, nice words,

00:22:30.250 --> 00:22:32.200 align:middle line:90%
but wow, my heart hurts.

00:22:32.200 --> 00:22:33.160 align:middle line:90%
My guts hurt.

00:22:33.160 --> 00:22:34.225 align:middle line:90%
I want to run.

00:22:34.225 --> 00:22:37.210 align:middle line:84%
Pay attention because you're
getting conflicting information

00:22:37.210 --> 00:22:38.950 align:middle line:90%
that's in a subtle field.

00:22:38.950 --> 00:22:42.760 align:middle line:84%
And I mean, this is
really hard because we

00:22:42.760 --> 00:22:45.400 align:middle line:84%
have to know started detaching
our intellect from everything

00:22:45.400 --> 00:22:49.270 align:middle line:84%
we've been told is true into
a level of true discernment,

00:22:49.270 --> 00:22:50.920 align:middle line:84%
which gets us back
to the original part

00:22:50.920 --> 00:22:52.360 align:middle line:90%
of the conversation.

00:22:52.360 --> 00:22:54.340 align:middle line:84%
When you keep reducing,
reducing, reducing,

00:22:54.340 --> 00:22:55.900 align:middle line:90%
we go to desire.

00:22:55.900 --> 00:22:57.960 align:middle line:90%
Crowley calls it will.

00:22:57.960 --> 00:23:01.170 align:middle line:84%
And desire fueled by will
is a very, very powerful.

00:23:01.170 --> 00:23:02.650 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Yes, yes.

00:23:02.650 --> 00:23:05.830 align:middle line:84%
I would say desire
fueled by will is,

00:23:05.830 --> 00:23:08.770 align:middle line:90%
it's the primeval form of magic.

00:23:08.770 --> 00:23:10.960 align:middle line:84%
It's the deepest
part of ourselves.

00:23:10.960 --> 00:23:13.720 align:middle line:84%
You know I would suspect
that all of your viewers

00:23:13.720 --> 00:23:16.330 align:middle line:84%
probably can identify
a period of time

00:23:16.330 --> 00:23:19.060 align:middle line:84%
in life where they said
to themselves, maybe

00:23:19.060 --> 00:23:21.370 align:middle line:84%
when they were very young,
maybe when they were older,

00:23:21.370 --> 00:23:22.820 align:middle line:90%
I know exactly what I want.

00:23:22.820 --> 00:23:24.790 align:middle line:84%
I know exactly what
I have to go for.

00:23:24.790 --> 00:23:29.350 align:middle line:84%
And I would always ask people
to hold onto that recollection.

00:23:29.350 --> 00:23:31.270 align:middle line:84%
Think about what the
circumstances were

00:23:31.270 --> 00:23:35.050 align:middle line:84%
when you experienced it and ask
yourself, can I cultivate this?

00:23:35.050 --> 00:23:36.520 align:middle line:90%
Because there's magic in that.

00:23:36.520 --> 00:23:39.220 align:middle line:84%
And I've experienced
it myself and recently.

00:23:39.220 --> 00:23:40.630 align:middle line:90%
You can't always cultivate it.

00:23:40.630 --> 00:23:42.250 align:middle line:84%
It can't always
be grasped again.

00:23:42.250 --> 00:23:43.630 align:middle line:90%
But sometimes it can.

00:23:43.630 --> 00:23:46.840 align:middle line:10%
And I know I had an experience
myself about 20 years ago,

00:23:46.840 --> 00:23:48.910 align:middle line:10%
where I walked to the
top of a stone tower that

00:23:48.910 --> 00:23:52.430 align:middle line:10%
was on the banks of the Charles
River in Westin, Massachusetts.

00:23:52.430 --> 00:23:54.430 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't supposed to be
inside this stone tower.

00:23:54.430 --> 00:23:56.260 align:middle line:84%
It was covered with
grating and stuff.

00:23:56.260 --> 00:23:57.513 align:middle line:90%
But I had to go inside.

00:23:57.513 --> 00:23:58.930 align:middle line:84%
And I got to the
top of this tower

00:23:58.930 --> 00:24:01.760 align:middle line:84%
and I looked out over the
Charles, and I said to myself,

00:24:01.760 --> 00:24:02.740 align:middle line:90%
I want to be a writer.

00:24:02.740 --> 00:24:04.662 align:middle line:84%
I want to be an
established author.

00:24:04.662 --> 00:24:05.870 align:middle line:90%
And something went out of me.

00:24:05.870 --> 00:24:08.270 align:middle line:84%
And it was the most
magical moment of my life.

00:24:08.270 --> 00:24:10.600 align:middle line:84%
I know people listening
have had those experiences.

00:24:10.600 --> 00:24:11.730 align:middle line:90%
Watch for those.

00:24:11.730 --> 00:24:12.530 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree.

00:24:12.530 --> 00:24:16.450 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, I do conferences,
sometimes, very rarely,

00:24:16.450 --> 00:24:18.370 align:middle line:84%
where I'll take a
small group of people

00:24:18.370 --> 00:24:21.520 align:middle line:84%
and I'll take them into my home
for two, three days together.

00:24:21.520 --> 00:24:24.310 align:middle line:84%
And I do this one
particular meditation

00:24:24.310 --> 00:24:26.560 align:middle line:84%
that brings back the
magic of what you

00:24:26.560 --> 00:24:28.920 align:middle line:90%
desired at five, six years old.

00:24:28.920 --> 00:24:30.220 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Brilliant,

00:24:30.220 --> 00:24:31.053 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Brilliant.

00:24:31.053 --> 00:24:34.990 align:middle line:84%
Because we're much closer
at that age to the desires

00:24:34.990 --> 00:24:38.920 align:middle line:84%
we came in with, even if it's
not literally the feeling

00:24:38.920 --> 00:24:41.230 align:middle line:84%
that fueled that
desire at that age

00:24:41.230 --> 00:24:44.260 align:middle line:84%
and reconnecting with
that particular feeling

00:24:44.260 --> 00:24:46.510 align:middle line:84%
may or may not be
associated with that thing

00:24:46.510 --> 00:24:48.310 align:middle line:84%
that they love
doing at that time.

00:24:48.310 --> 00:24:51.940 align:middle line:84%
But it's going back and tracing
when what moments in my life

00:24:51.940 --> 00:24:53.820 align:middle line:90%
have I felt that feeling.

00:24:53.820 --> 00:24:55.360 align:middle line:90%
That's the feeling of passion.

00:24:55.360 --> 00:24:56.580 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: That's wonderful.

00:24:56.580 --> 00:24:59.290 align:middle line:84%
You know, this is something I
talk about in one of my books.

00:24:59.290 --> 00:25:01.570 align:middle line:84%
The philosopher
Goethe had a principle

00:25:01.570 --> 00:25:06.250 align:middle line:84%
that what you wish for when
you're very, very young

00:25:06.250 --> 00:25:08.590 align:middle line:84%
will come upon you in
waves when you're old.

00:25:08.590 --> 00:25:09.890 align:middle line:90%
So be careful.

00:25:09.890 --> 00:25:11.800 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people hear that
and they want to argue with it

00:25:11.800 --> 00:25:12.700 align:middle line:90%
and say, well, wait a minute.

00:25:12.700 --> 00:25:14.770 align:middle line:84%
There's lots of things I
wish for I haven't got.

00:25:14.770 --> 00:25:16.870 align:middle line:84%
And I would always say,
take some time with that.

00:25:16.870 --> 00:25:18.520 align:middle line:90%
Peel back the onion.

00:25:18.520 --> 00:25:21.940 align:middle line:84%
Because you may find
an uncanny congruity

00:25:21.940 --> 00:25:25.180 align:middle line:84%
between your fantasies when you
were even as young as age three

00:25:25.180 --> 00:25:28.150 align:middle line:84%
or four and what you're
living out right now.

00:25:28.150 --> 00:25:29.530 align:middle line:90%
We're very forgetful.

00:25:29.530 --> 00:25:32.800 align:middle line:84%
And with intervals of time we
fail to make connections, just

00:25:32.800 --> 00:25:33.880 align:middle line:90%
human nature.

00:25:33.880 --> 00:25:36.130 align:middle line:84%
But if you really allow the
onion to be peeled back,

00:25:36.130 --> 00:25:40.030 align:middle line:84%
you might find an extraordinary
symmetry between the earliest

00:25:40.030 --> 00:25:41.975 align:middle line:90%
fantasies and present life.

00:25:41.975 --> 00:25:42.850 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:25:42.850 --> 00:25:45.250 align:middle line:84%
I mean, in my life has
been quite literal.

00:25:45.250 --> 00:25:47.740 align:middle line:84%
I mean, my earliest
fantasies were all artistic,

00:25:47.740 --> 00:25:49.860 align:middle line:90%
but especially dancing.

00:25:49.860 --> 00:25:52.180 align:middle line:84%
You know going borrowing
someone's coffee table

00:25:52.180 --> 00:25:54.910 align:middle line:84%
book at five to teach myself
ballet, because no one would

00:25:54.910 --> 00:25:56.290 align:middle line:90%
give me lessons.

00:25:56.290 --> 00:25:58.450 align:middle line:84%
But then again, picking
up ballet as an adult,

00:25:58.450 --> 00:26:01.100 align:middle line:84%
I was taking ballet
again right before COVID.

00:26:01.100 --> 00:26:03.470 align:middle line:84%
You know, tango
dancing, tap dancing,

00:26:03.470 --> 00:26:06.160 align:middle line:84%
you know, something about
having communication

00:26:06.160 --> 00:26:09.400 align:middle line:84%
moved through the body,
because I wasn't very I wasn't

00:26:09.400 --> 00:26:11.560 align:middle line:90%
very open and communicative.

00:26:11.560 --> 00:26:15.280 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't speak with my
mouth, but my body could speak.

00:26:15.280 --> 00:26:17.530 align:middle line:84%
And so I find that that's
facilitated all kinds

00:26:17.530 --> 00:26:18.700 align:middle line:90%
of communication sense.

00:26:18.700 --> 00:26:21.755 align:middle line:84%
And even being a journalist
and a film producer, when

00:26:21.755 --> 00:26:23.130 align:middle line:84%
I was very young,
I thought, god,

00:26:23.130 --> 00:26:25.420 align:middle line:90%
could a woman direct a film?

00:26:25.420 --> 00:26:29.020 align:middle line:84%
And 20, 30 years later I'm on
a mountaintop with my crew.

00:26:29.020 --> 00:26:32.715 align:middle line:84%
It's like oh my god, I had
this fantasy as a girl.

00:26:32.715 --> 00:26:34.840 align:middle line:84%
Tell me some of those for
you and some other people

00:26:34.840 --> 00:26:37.465 align:middle line:84%
because this is exciting when we
start, because people watching

00:26:37.465 --> 00:26:39.520 align:middle line:84%
right now are, oh
my god, I remember

00:26:39.520 --> 00:26:41.985 align:middle line:90%
what I was excited about.

00:26:41.985 --> 00:26:43.610 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: I'll
share it very frankly.

00:26:43.610 --> 00:26:46.720 align:middle line:84%
When I was a kid just
from the youngest age,

00:26:46.720 --> 00:26:49.270 align:middle line:84%
like let's say age
four, I vividly

00:26:49.270 --> 00:26:51.160 align:middle line:84%
remember that when
we were playing--

00:26:51.160 --> 00:26:53.160 align:middle line:84%
I was playing some kind
of game with my friends,

00:26:53.160 --> 00:26:57.010 align:middle line:84%
whether it was an army game
or cowboys or whatever it was,

00:26:57.010 --> 00:26:59.440 align:middle line:84%
I was internally
imagining that I

00:26:59.440 --> 00:27:03.850 align:middle line:84%
was playing the part of a cowboy
or playing the part of an army

00:27:03.850 --> 00:27:07.850 align:middle line:84%
guy in a movie, in a TV show and
that there was a camera on me.

00:27:07.850 --> 00:27:10.270 align:middle line:84%
Now, I didn't disclose
this to my friends.

00:27:10.270 --> 00:27:12.370 align:middle line:84%
And they were surely having
their own experiences.

00:27:12.370 --> 00:27:16.060 align:middle line:84%
But that was part of my
earliest stock of memories.

00:27:16.060 --> 00:27:18.520 align:middle line:84%
And I look at my life
today, and very often I

00:27:18.520 --> 00:27:20.770 align:middle line:84%
am in front of cameras and
I am in front of audiences.

00:27:20.770 --> 00:27:22.510 align:middle line:90%
I am in front of microphones.

00:27:22.510 --> 00:27:24.640 align:middle line:84%
It didn't come about
in exactly the way

00:27:24.640 --> 00:27:26.120 align:middle line:90%
that I could have imagined.

00:27:26.120 --> 00:27:27.440 align:middle line:90%
But it came about.

00:27:27.440 --> 00:27:29.170 align:middle line:90%
And it did so decisively.

00:27:29.170 --> 00:27:31.240 align:middle line:84%
And I really want people
to turn their minds back

00:27:31.240 --> 00:27:33.430 align:middle line:90%
to those earliest fantasies.

00:27:33.430 --> 00:27:36.100 align:middle line:84%
There is so much information
there about who we are

00:27:36.100 --> 00:27:37.900 align:middle line:90%
and who we must be.

00:27:37.900 --> 00:27:38.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:27:38.870 --> 00:27:40.940 align:middle line:84%
And so, I encourage
everybody right now just,

00:27:40.940 --> 00:27:42.940 align:middle line:84%
even if you have to hit
pause, go back and think

00:27:42.940 --> 00:27:45.830 align:middle line:84%
about it before we even go
on with this conversation.

00:27:45.830 --> 00:27:46.630 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:27:46.630 --> 00:27:48.430 align:middle line:84%
We have a lot of
places we can go here.

00:27:48.430 --> 00:27:50.680 align:middle line:84%
But one of them is, you've
been in Egypt recently.

00:27:50.680 --> 00:27:52.555 align:middle line:84%
And I was going to
use a segue to that,

00:27:52.555 --> 00:27:55.600 align:middle line:84%
that the whole notion of
this black and white, light

00:27:55.600 --> 00:27:58.060 align:middle line:84%
and dark, you know, white
magic, black magic, that

00:27:58.060 --> 00:28:00.820 align:middle line:84%
dates back thousands
and thousands of years,

00:28:00.820 --> 00:28:02.390 align:middle line:90%
these principles.

00:28:02.390 --> 00:28:05.080 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things that
you were talking about

00:28:05.080 --> 00:28:08.950 align:middle line:84%
was the notion that you
have set and Horus embracing

00:28:08.950 --> 00:28:11.860 align:middle line:90%
one another in this statuary.

00:28:11.860 --> 00:28:14.530 align:middle line:90%
Talk about that.

00:28:14.530 --> 00:28:17.710 align:middle line:84%
And then we'll get into Egypt,
the culture, and everything.

00:28:17.710 --> 00:28:20.620 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Horus is seen as
sort of the Redeemer figure

00:28:20.620 --> 00:28:22.030 align:middle line:90%
in ancient Egyptian culture.

00:28:22.030 --> 00:28:25.570 align:middle line:84%
Set is seen sometimes as
the adversarial figure,

00:28:25.570 --> 00:28:27.220 align:middle line:90%
the satanic figure.

00:28:27.220 --> 00:28:29.620 align:middle line:84%
And one of the old
kingdom pharaohs

00:28:29.620 --> 00:28:32.080 align:middle line:84%
was trying to unite
Upper and Lower Egypt,

00:28:32.080 --> 00:28:36.970 align:middle line:84%
and he instructed his artists to
depict images of Set and Horus

00:28:36.970 --> 00:28:38.410 align:middle line:90%
embracing one another.

00:28:38.410 --> 00:28:41.008 align:middle line:84%
And I was just overwhelmed
when I saw these base reliefs.

00:28:41.008 --> 00:28:42.550 align:middle line:84%
Because we don't
see that very often.

00:28:42.550 --> 00:28:43.120 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I have not that.

00:28:43.120 --> 00:28:44.620 align:middle line:90%
That's why it really caught me.

00:28:44.620 --> 00:28:45.670 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: They're rare.

00:28:45.670 --> 00:28:47.510 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, there's
the whole human situation.

00:28:47.510 --> 00:28:48.430 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What dynasty
was that, which pharaoh?

00:28:48.430 --> 00:28:49.630 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: It was one of
the old kingdom dynasties

00:28:49.630 --> 00:28:51.250 align:middle line:90%
but I don't recall the pharaoh.

00:28:51.250 --> 00:28:53.332 align:middle line:84%
And it's in the Egyptian
National Museum.

00:28:53.332 --> 00:28:54.790 align:middle line:84%
It's somewhere off
in the basement.

00:28:54.790 --> 00:28:56.220 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's not
very widely seen.

00:28:56.220 --> 00:28:56.890 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: In Cairo?

00:28:56.890 --> 00:28:57.765 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: In Cairo.

00:28:57.765 --> 00:28:59.560 align:middle line:90%
But it's absolute magnificent.

00:28:59.560 --> 00:29:01.570 align:middle line:84%
I have some images
which I can post online

00:29:01.570 --> 00:29:03.310 align:middle line:90%
for people, which I will do.

00:29:03.310 --> 00:29:05.890 align:middle line:84%
And it's the whole
human situation.

00:29:05.890 --> 00:29:07.870 align:middle line:84%
We have to embrace these
different sides of us,

00:29:07.870 --> 00:29:09.190 align:middle line:90%
because they're all us.

00:29:09.190 --> 00:29:09.990 align:middle line:90%
They're all us.

00:29:09.990 --> 00:29:12.885 align:middle line:84%
That doesn't mean throwing
reciprocity out the window.

00:29:12.885 --> 00:29:15.010 align:middle line:84%
But we can't be divorced
from these different sides

00:29:15.010 --> 00:29:15.810 align:middle line:90%
to ourselves.

00:29:15.810 --> 00:29:17.690 align:middle line:84%
Somewhere along the
line, the human story

00:29:17.690 --> 00:29:22.160 align:middle line:84%
got broken down into a white
magic, black magic dichotomy.

00:29:22.160 --> 00:29:24.670 align:middle line:84%
And we're afraid of the
fact that we're both.

00:29:24.670 --> 00:29:25.730 align:middle line:90%
We're both.

00:29:25.730 --> 00:29:27.560 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And that's what I like
so much about the story you're

00:29:27.560 --> 00:29:28.580 align:middle line:90%
telling about yourself.

00:29:28.580 --> 00:29:33.350 align:middle line:84%
You can appreciate what Aleister
Crowley brought to the front

00:29:33.350 --> 00:29:36.635 align:middle line:84%
in terms of the way in which
humans can use their desire

00:29:36.635 --> 00:29:38.137 align:middle line:90%
and their will for outcome.

00:29:38.137 --> 00:29:40.470 align:middle line:84%
At the same time, you're not
going to follow his ethics.

00:29:40.470 --> 00:29:43.220 align:middle line:84%
You're going to apply it with
a very highly developed sense

00:29:43.220 --> 00:29:44.090 align:middle line:90%
of ethics.

00:29:44.090 --> 00:29:47.810 align:middle line:84%
And yet, right
now in this world,

00:29:47.810 --> 00:29:49.520 align:middle line:84%
I've never seen
more polarization.

00:29:49.520 --> 00:29:50.478 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Absolutely.

00:29:50.478 --> 00:29:52.700 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: If you can
make a person wrong,

00:29:52.700 --> 00:29:54.730 align:middle line:90%
you're going to make you wrong.

00:29:54.730 --> 00:29:59.380 align:middle line:84%
And there's a deep need to have
I don't even understand fully,

00:29:59.380 --> 00:30:02.940 align:middle line:84%
this need for such
re-entrenched identity,

00:30:02.940 --> 00:30:06.220 align:middle line:84%
that everything outside
of that is simply wrong.

00:30:06.220 --> 00:30:09.220 align:middle line:84%
What you're asking for, what
we're talking about here

00:30:09.220 --> 00:30:11.155 align:middle line:90%
is literally to throw that away.

00:30:11.155 --> 00:30:12.280 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: That's my wish.

00:30:12.280 --> 00:30:14.470 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: How does
that happen in such

00:30:14.470 --> 00:30:16.157 align:middle line:90%
an incredibly polarized world?

00:30:16.157 --> 00:30:17.740 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: It's
interesting you know,

00:30:17.740 --> 00:30:19.532 align:middle line:84%
obviously some of the
problems we're facing

00:30:19.532 --> 00:30:20.950 align:middle line:90%
have to do with social media.

00:30:20.950 --> 00:30:22.840 align:middle line:90%
Human nature hasn't changed.

00:30:22.840 --> 00:30:24.430 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Media
and social media.

00:30:24.430 --> 00:30:25.888 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Media
and social media.

00:30:25.888 --> 00:30:28.480 align:middle line:84%
There's something about the
anonymity of social media

00:30:28.480 --> 00:30:29.913 align:middle line:90%
that I don't like.

00:30:29.913 --> 00:30:31.330 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It brings
up a meanness.

00:30:31.330 --> 00:30:32.163 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: It does.

00:30:32.163 --> 00:30:33.820 align:middle line:84%
It brings up a
meanness and there's

00:30:33.820 --> 00:30:37.450 align:middle line:84%
a disinhibition of the wrong
kind that encourages people,

00:30:37.450 --> 00:30:41.560 align:middle line:84%
sometimes anonymously,
sometimes not, to make

00:30:41.560 --> 00:30:44.750 align:middle line:84%
a withering and nasty and
sarcastic comment at will,

00:30:44.750 --> 00:30:48.160 align:middle line:90%
24/7, always and everywhere.

00:30:48.160 --> 00:30:50.770 align:middle line:84%
And it's really problematic
because it's not

00:30:50.770 --> 00:30:52.280 align:middle line:90%
accompanied by bravery.

00:30:52.280 --> 00:30:53.080 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:30:53.080 --> 00:30:54.790 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: There isn't
a commensurate bravery.

00:30:54.790 --> 00:30:56.665 align:middle line:84%
If you're going to get
up in somebody's face,

00:30:56.665 --> 00:30:58.490 align:middle line:84%
that may or may
not be a good idea.

00:30:58.490 --> 00:31:01.390 align:middle line:84%
But if you're going to do
it, at least bear witness.

00:31:01.390 --> 00:31:03.470 align:middle line:84%
At least be who
you actually are.

00:31:03.470 --> 00:31:06.130 align:middle line:84%
But when you're hiding
behind an anonymous handle

00:31:06.130 --> 00:31:09.460 align:middle line:84%
or when you're functioning at a
social remove or the perception

00:31:09.460 --> 00:31:11.710 align:middle line:84%
of social remove, it's
kind of like everybody's

00:31:11.710 --> 00:31:14.890 align:middle line:84%
going all guns blazing
with no consequence.

00:31:14.890 --> 00:31:16.330 align:middle line:84%
But there are
consequences, which

00:31:16.330 --> 00:31:18.200 align:middle line:90%
is we've degraded one another.

00:31:18.200 --> 00:31:21.760 align:middle line:84%
And we've made sarcasm, which
has its uses, into the language

00:31:21.760 --> 00:31:23.140 align:middle line:90%
of everyday life.

00:31:23.140 --> 00:31:25.000 align:middle line:84%
I always tell
people, if you want

00:31:25.000 --> 00:31:28.000 align:middle line:84%
to stand more tall, if you
feel like you're suffering

00:31:28.000 --> 00:31:31.600 align:middle line:84%
from a poor self-image, give
yourself one hour in which you

00:31:31.600 --> 00:31:34.810 align:middle line:84%
desist from gossip,
humiliating other people,

00:31:34.810 --> 00:31:38.350 align:middle line:84%
or withering sarcasm, and see
if you don't stand more tall.

00:31:38.350 --> 00:31:39.220 align:middle line:90%
You will.

00:31:39.220 --> 00:31:40.630 align:middle line:90%
These things degrade us.

00:31:40.630 --> 00:31:41.710 align:middle line:90%
These things degrade us.

00:31:41.710 --> 00:31:42.710 align:middle line:90%
And people don't see it.

00:31:42.710 --> 00:31:45.130 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They don't and we
don't know how subtle it is

00:31:45.130 --> 00:31:47.570 align:middle line:84%
and how serious it
is in our own lives.

00:31:47.570 --> 00:31:48.370 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Right.

00:31:48.370 --> 00:31:49.210 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:31:49.210 --> 00:31:51.030 align:middle line:90%
It all--

00:31:51.030 --> 00:31:53.950 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Making even a little
dig like, oh, god, them again?

00:31:53.950 --> 00:31:54.880 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Exactly.

00:31:54.880 --> 00:31:57.070 align:middle line:84%
It does come back
to the individual.

00:31:57.070 --> 00:31:59.200 align:middle line:84%
I think there's a
faculty within us that's

00:31:59.200 --> 00:32:01.540 align:middle line:84%
sometimes called auto
suggestion, that we

00:32:01.540 --> 00:32:02.510 align:middle line:90%
are what we think.

00:32:02.510 --> 00:32:03.310 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:32:03.310 --> 00:32:06.850 align:middle line:84%
Auto suggestion, let's say, or
conditioning shape self-image.

00:32:06.850 --> 00:32:10.180 align:middle line:84%
We also are shaped by what
we're always saying and thinking

00:32:10.180 --> 00:32:11.230 align:middle line:90%
about other people.

00:32:11.230 --> 00:32:12.640 align:middle line:90%
We don't get a pass.

00:32:12.640 --> 00:32:16.260 align:middle line:84%
That auto suggest is a function
that reverberates back to us.

00:32:16.260 --> 00:32:18.250 align:middle line:84%
And I would venture
that other people

00:32:18.250 --> 00:32:19.570 align:middle line:90%
have had this experience.

00:32:19.570 --> 00:32:23.770 align:middle line:84%
If you go to lunch with somebody
who draws you into gossiping

00:32:23.770 --> 00:32:26.890 align:middle line:84%
and you spend 90 minutes
gossiping, just talking down

00:32:26.890 --> 00:32:28.780 align:middle line:84%
other people for
cheap thrills, you

00:32:28.780 --> 00:32:31.130 align:middle line:84%
will feel almost physically
sick after that lunch.

00:32:31.130 --> 00:32:31.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:32:31.570 --> 00:32:33.778 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: I've had that
experience, Listen to that.

00:32:33.778 --> 00:32:35.680 align:middle line:90%
That's valuable information.

00:32:35.680 --> 00:32:38.110 align:middle line:90%
Imagine what's going on 24/7.

00:32:38.110 --> 00:32:39.400 align:middle line:90%
But it can be unplugged from.

00:32:39.400 --> 00:32:40.270 align:middle line:90%
It is possible.

00:32:40.270 --> 00:32:41.860 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And there's
also a fine line

00:32:41.860 --> 00:32:44.440 align:middle line:84%
between sharing kind of
critical, uncomfortable

00:32:44.440 --> 00:32:46.270 align:middle line:90%
information and gossip.

00:32:46.270 --> 00:32:48.160 align:middle line:84%
So how do you even
make that discernment

00:32:48.160 --> 00:32:50.810 align:middle line:84%
because people need to know in
their bodies, how to discern.

00:32:50.810 --> 00:32:54.010 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Sure, listen, people
have to call out injustice

00:32:54.010 --> 00:32:54.850 align:middle line:90%
sometimes.

00:32:54.850 --> 00:32:57.032 align:middle line:84%
People have to air
problems sometimes.

00:32:57.032 --> 00:32:58.240 align:middle line:90%
We're going to have friction.

00:32:58.240 --> 00:32:59.897 align:middle line:84%
That's part of the
human situation.

00:32:59.897 --> 00:33:01.480 align:middle line:84%
And if you talk it
over with a friend,

00:33:01.480 --> 00:33:03.020 align:middle line:84%
you're going to be
representing your side

00:33:03.020 --> 00:33:04.690 align:middle line:84%
and they'll be representing
the other side.

00:33:04.690 --> 00:33:07.065 align:middle line:84%
I'm not saying that there's
not a place for that in life.

00:33:07.065 --> 00:33:08.080 align:middle line:90%
Of course there is.

00:33:08.080 --> 00:33:10.390 align:middle line:84%
But it's talking
down people in kind

00:33:10.390 --> 00:33:13.202 align:middle line:90%
of a wise ass kind of way--

00:33:13.202 --> 00:33:15.160 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That makes you
feel somehow superior.

00:33:15.160 --> 00:33:17.290 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Superior, exactly.

00:33:17.290 --> 00:33:19.750 align:middle line:84%
Taking pleasure at
other people's pain

00:33:19.750 --> 00:33:23.620 align:middle line:84%
or suffering, taking
an attitude that--

00:33:23.620 --> 00:33:24.920 align:middle line:90%
almost it's entertainment.

00:33:24.920 --> 00:33:27.102 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's smear
as entertainment.

