Think of the possibilities
that presents to us.

00:38:44.490 --> 00:38:44.790 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:38:44.790 --> 00:38:45.832 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: It's amazing.

00:38:45.832 --> 00:38:48.310 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Back to pure mind,
pure desire, pure will.

00:38:48.310 --> 00:38:49.810 align:middle line:84%
And now there was
another study, it

00:38:49.810 --> 00:38:51.733 align:middle line:84%
had to do with
maids, hotel maids.

00:38:51.733 --> 00:38:52.900 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: The hotel maids.

00:38:52.900 --> 00:38:54.150 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Let's talk about it.

00:38:54.150 --> 00:38:56.530 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Absolutely
mind blowing.

00:38:56.530 --> 00:38:58.570 align:middle line:84%
People are going to
think I'm making this up

00:38:58.570 --> 00:39:00.370 align:middle line:84%
and I encourage
them to go online,

00:39:00.370 --> 00:39:03.130 align:middle line:84%
put in the search terms,
find the scientific journals

00:39:03.130 --> 00:39:04.510 align:middle line:90%
that this was written about in.

00:39:04.510 --> 00:39:06.900 align:middle line:84%
And call me out if I'm
exaggerating any of it.

00:39:06.900 --> 00:39:08.452 align:middle line:90%
Call me out.

00:39:08.452 --> 00:39:09.910 align:middle line:10%
There was a
psychologist at Harvard

00:39:09.910 --> 00:39:12.910 align:middle line:10%
named Ellen Langer who did
a study several years ago

00:39:12.910 --> 00:39:14.680 align:middle line:10%
with a group of hotel maids.

00:39:14.680 --> 00:39:17.320 align:middle line:84%
She divided the subjects,
as in most of these studies,

00:39:17.320 --> 00:39:21.430 align:middle line:84%
into a control group, who
just went about their business

00:39:21.430 --> 00:39:24.100 align:middle line:84%
as normal, and
then a study group.

00:39:24.100 --> 00:39:26.620 align:middle line:84%
Langer and her colleagues
told the study group

00:39:26.620 --> 00:39:29.410 align:middle line:84%
the truth, which is
that the work they're

00:39:29.410 --> 00:39:31.700 align:middle line:84%
doing every day
as hotel maids has

00:39:31.700 --> 00:39:35.020 align:middle line:84%
aerobic and anaerobic benefit,
and did they know that?

00:39:35.020 --> 00:39:37.480 align:middle line:84%
Most of the maids said,
well no, I didn't know that.

00:39:37.480 --> 00:39:39.700 align:middle line:84%
And Langer and her
colleagues said, well, yeah.

00:39:39.700 --> 00:39:41.020 align:middle line:90%
Check this out.

00:39:41.020 --> 00:39:43.420 align:middle line:84%
You're pushing around
vacuums all day long.

00:39:43.420 --> 00:39:44.470 align:middle line:90%
You're changing linen.

00:39:44.470 --> 00:39:45.370 align:middle line:90%
You're moving around.

00:39:45.370 --> 00:39:46.730 align:middle line:90%
You're on your hands and knees.

00:39:46.730 --> 00:39:48.070 align:middle line:90%
You're pushing a cart.

00:39:48.070 --> 00:39:51.550 align:middle line:84%
These things have aerobic
and anaerobic benefit.

00:39:51.550 --> 00:39:56.570 align:middle line:84%
Six weeks in, the control
group showed no change.

00:39:56.570 --> 00:40:00.740 align:middle line:84%
The study group
showed weight loss,

00:40:00.740 --> 00:40:05.570 align:middle line:84%
lowered blood pressure, greater
flexibility, and greater muscle

00:40:05.570 --> 00:40:06.800 align:middle line:90%
to fat ratio.

00:40:06.800 --> 00:40:08.780 align:middle line:90%
They had done nothing different.

00:40:08.780 --> 00:40:11.297 align:middle line:84%
Langer and her team was
monitoring their activities.

00:40:11.297 --> 00:40:13.130 align:middle line:84%
There was no difference
in their activities.

00:40:13.130 --> 00:40:16.930 align:middle line:84%
Just knowing the truth,
which is that their jobs had

00:40:16.930 --> 00:40:20.060 align:middle line:84%
aerobic and anaerobic benefit,
made a concrete difference

00:40:20.060 --> 00:40:22.340 align:middle line:84%
in their health,
measurable, measurable,

00:40:22.340 --> 00:40:24.620 align:middle line:84%
even to the extent
of weight loss,

00:40:24.620 --> 00:40:27.590 align:middle line:84%
muscle tone, lowered
hypertension.

00:40:27.590 --> 00:40:29.130 align:middle line:90%
It's just incredible.

00:40:29.130 --> 00:40:30.505 align:middle line:84%
These people were
told the truth.

00:40:30.505 --> 00:40:31.880 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And it
wasn't that they

00:40:31.880 --> 00:40:33.500 align:middle line:84%
had to go into a
deep belief system.

00:40:33.500 --> 00:40:35.150 align:middle line:90%
It was just an understanding.

00:40:35.150 --> 00:40:36.000 align:middle line:90%
Oh, OK, sure.

00:40:36.000 --> 00:40:36.800 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:40:36.800 --> 00:40:37.610 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Just an acceptance.

00:40:37.610 --> 00:40:39.320 align:middle line:84%
They monitored their
activities carefully.

00:40:39.320 --> 00:40:41.000 align:middle line:84%
There was no change
in their activities.

00:40:41.000 --> 00:40:43.820 align:middle line:84%
But knowledge itself,
accurate knowledge

00:40:43.820 --> 00:40:45.030 align:middle line:90%
of what they were doing.

00:40:45.030 --> 00:40:48.410 align:middle line:84%
I mean, listen the phrase has
to be used, mind over matter.

00:40:48.410 --> 00:40:49.370 align:middle line:90%
Mind over matter.

00:40:49.370 --> 00:40:51.050 align:middle line:90%
That's not an exaggeration.

00:40:51.050 --> 00:40:53.240 align:middle line:90%
No one challenges this data.

00:40:53.240 --> 00:40:56.190 align:middle line:84%
They might challenge the
implications of the data.

00:40:56.190 --> 00:40:57.773 align:middle line:90%
But those are the implications.

00:40:57.773 --> 00:41:00.440 align:middle line:84%
And there's many other things in
neuroplasticity, where thoughts

00:41:00.440 --> 00:41:02.810 align:middle line:84%
change the neural
pathways through which

00:41:02.810 --> 00:41:04.670 align:middle line:90%
electrical impulses travel.

00:41:04.670 --> 00:41:08.090 align:middle line:84%
The designer of neuroplasticity,
a psychologist at UCLA,

00:41:08.090 --> 00:41:10.130 align:middle line:84%
Jeffrey Schwartz,
he's brave enough

00:41:10.130 --> 00:41:12.530 align:middle line:84%
to say, yes, this is
actually mind over matter.

00:41:12.530 --> 00:41:14.240 align:middle line:90%
This is mind over matter.

00:41:14.240 --> 00:41:16.413 align:middle line:84%
We're seeing this
in our generation.

00:41:16.413 --> 00:41:18.830 align:middle line:84%
So to say that we lead an extra
physical existence, that's

00:41:18.830 --> 00:41:20.067 align:middle line:90%
not a far out statement.

00:41:20.067 --> 00:41:20.900 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It is not.

